detail_description: St. Nikolai Church in Kiel has a rich history, with its construction dating back to the city's founding in 1242. The church has undergone several reconstructions and extensions over the years, including a restoration after being devastated by Allied bomb raids during World War II. Despite the destruction, ecclesiastical treasures and artworks had been removed prior to the bombings. In 1950, the church was reconstructed using modern elements and materials.
name: St. Nikolai Church

excerpt: Free-entry gardens organized by climate also featuring greenhouses with desert & tropical plants.
detail_description: Nestled within the Kiel University campus, the Botanical Garden is a stunning natural and cultural monument with a history dating back 350 years. This hidden gem boasts an impressive collection of approximately 14,000 plant species, making it an ideal spot for both scientific research and student training. The garden features greenhouses showcasing desert and tropical plants, offering visitors a captivating experience that seamlessly blends education, conservation, and breathtaking natural beauty.
name: Botanical Garden

excerpt: War memorial with tower & observation deck, built in 1936 originally to honour World War I sailors.
detail_description: The Naval Memorial, also known as the Laboe Naval Memorial, is a significant war memorial featuring a tower and observation deck. Originally built in 1936 to honor sailors of World War I, it now symbolizes all seafarers who lost their lives in both world wars. The towering structure offers a small exhibition on the ground floor and stunning panoramic views from its platform.
name: Naval Memorial

excerpt: 17th-century zoological museum with dinosaur skeletons & interactive exhibits in imposing building.
detail_description: The Zoological Museum of Kiel University is housed in an impressive 17th-century building designed by renowned architect Martin Gropius. Its collections, dating back to the 1600s, feature a remarkable exhibit in the main hall showcasing 13 suspended whale skeletons. The museum offers interactive displays on evolution and biodiversity, including marine life with a focus on whale species. Visitors can explore the latest marine research findings through 'The Future Ocean' exhibit.
name: Zoological Museum of Kiel University

excerpt: Boathouses & marinas line this waterfront drive with a bike lane & pedestrian promenade.
detail_description: Kiellinie is a picturesque waterfront drive along the Kiel Fjord, featuring boathouses, marinas, and a dedicated bike lane and pedestrian promenade. The route offers stunning views of the fjord and takes you past various attractions such as the Heimholtz Centre for Ocean Research with its outdoor seal aquarium. During Kiel Week, the promenade comes alive with concert stages and sailing races in the fjord.
name: Kiellinie

excerpt: Kiel is a port city on Germany’s Baltic Sea coast. In the old town, the rebuilt, medieval St. Nikolai Church hosts classical concerts. Holstenstrasse and Dänische Strasse are streets lined with shops. Along the Kiel Fjord, the Maritime Museum displays model ships and nautical instruments in a former fish auction hall. Cruise ships dock at the Ostseekai Terminal in Germania Harbor.
detail_description: Kiel, a vibrant port city located on the Baltic Sea coast in Germany, offers a blend of historical charm and maritime attractions. The old town features the reconstructed St. Nikolai Church where classical concerts are held, while Holstenstrasse and Dänische Strasse boast an array of shops for visitors to explore. Along the picturesque Kiel Fjord, the Maritime Museum housed in a former fish auction hall showcases model ships and nautical instruments.
name: Kiel

excerpt: Kiel's maritime history is detailed through artifacts & models in this former municipal fish hall.
detail_description: The Kiel Maritime Museum, located in a former fish auction hall, offers a detailed look at the city's maritime history. The exhibits explore the significance of the harbor, navy, dockyards, and sailing through artifacts such as fishing boats, nautical instruments, and maritime-themed paintings. Additionally, visitors can admire a collection of antiques donated by a private collector. Nearby stands the reconstructed St.
name: Kiel Maritime Museum Fish Market & Museum Bridge

excerpt: Compact outdoor aquarium, best known for its seals, also exhibiting a variety of fish & crustaceans.
detail_description: Aquarium GEOMAR is a compact outdoor aquarium located in Kiel, offering a diverse range of marine life. It is best known for its seals and features various fish and crustaceans from the Baltic, Mediterranean, and tropical regions. The aquarium provides an immersive experience with lifelike environments showcasing Nordic and tropical swimmers. Visitors can explore the informative exhibits to learn about the diversity of marine creatures and their habitats.
name: Aquarium GEOMAR

detail_description: Kieler Brauerei am Alten Markt offers a rustic setting and a variety of culinary delights for the palate and senses. Visitors can savor German specialties in the brewery's cozy spaces and even pour their own beer at the table, immersing themselves in brewery culture while being surprised by the diverse beer selection. The brewery revives the tradition of small breweries and pubs that once thrived in the bustling harbor town, brewing craft beer since 1988.
name: Kieler Brauerei am Alten Markt

excerpt: Historical & technical submarine museum housed in a German U-boat active in World War II.
detail_description: German submarine U-995 is a historical and technical museum located on Laboe beach, housed in a World War II-era U-boat. This Nazi Germany submarine was damaged in 1944 and later used by the Norwegian navy until the 1960s. Today, it offers visitors a glimpse into its tight interior, including the engine room, cabins, control stations, and torpedo tubes. It is one of the few remaining intact U-boats and sits next to the Laboe Naval Memorial.
name: German submarine U-995

excerpt: Popular park with a duck pond, playground & large, grassy field, with areas for picnics & BBQs.
detail_description: Schrevenpark is a beloved destination in Kiel, offering a serene atmosphere and various attractions for visitors. The park features a charming duck pond, expansive grassy fields ideal for picnics and barbecues, and well-maintained playgrounds for children. It is also known for hosting concerts during festive seasons. Visitors can relax by the water, observe waterfowl, or fly kites while adhering to summer grilling regulations.
name: Schrevenpark

detail_description: Kieler Woche, also known as Kiel Week, is a major event in Germany that attracts between 600 and 800,000 visitors annually. The city of Kiel, also called 'the sailing city,' offers ample opportunities for maritime experiences. The Kieler Canal, the busiest of its kind globally, provides a unique view of giant ships. During the event, there are numerous attractions and around 100 dining options available.
name: Kieler Woche Marketing

detail_description: Hiroshima Park, located in the heart of Kiel, Germany, offers a peaceful retreat with its serene atmosphere and beautiful natural surroundings. The park features large shade trees and a tranquil water edge where visitors can relax and unwind. Named in honor of the tragic events of WWII, the park provides a place for quiet contemplation and reflection. Visitors can enjoy observing bird life around the lovely lake while lounging on deck chairs or sunbeds.
name: Hiroshimapark

excerpt: Bright, upbeat shopping mall with 2 floors of stores, including a popular, discount supermarket.
detail_description: Citti-Park Kiel is a vibrant shopping mall featuring two floors of over 90 shops and boutiques, offering the latest fashion trends and special deals. It's the largest shopping complex in Kiel, housing a variety of stores including clothing, shoes, groceries, electronics, bookstores, cafes and restaurants. The mall provides ample parking space and clean facilities with seating areas for relaxation. Visitors can find an array of food options and necessities while enjoying excellent customer service.
name: Citti-Park Kiel

detail_description: Nestled in the heart of Kiel, the Kiel Opera House (Theatre Kiel) stands as a historic gem that has been captivating audiences for over a century. This iconic venue is not only renowned for its stunning architecture but also serves as a vibrant hub for opera and ballet performances. Visitors can immerse themselves in an array of shows, from grand operatic productions to contemporary theater, all without the constraints of a strict dress code—just come as you are and enjoy!
name: Kiel Opera House (Theatre Kiel)

detail_description: Kieler Stadt- und Schifffahrtsmuseum offers a unique experience where visitors can immerse themselves in the history of Kiel. The museum provides an opportunity to learn about the city's past and its maritime heritage. After enjoying a relaxing time with coffee or tea while watching cruise ships, one can explore the museum to delve into Kiel's rich maritime history. It is a popular destination for those interested in gaining insights into the city's past and its connection to shipping.
name: Kieler Stadt- und Schifffahrtsmuseum

detail_description: Hörn Bridge in Kiel is a sight to behold with its unique three-segment bascule mechanism that folds on one side, creating an N shape when raised. This drawbridge offers a fascinating spectacle as it allows ships to pass through, providing visitors with the opportunity to see arriving and departing cruise ships and other boats. Crossing the bridge leads to an area filled with amusement rides like rollercoasters and carousels, making it a lively spot for entertainment.
name: Hörn Bridge

detail_description: Flandernbunker, located in the German naval harbour of Kiel, holds a fascinating history from the final years of World War II. This site served as a secret hideout for leaders anticipating airstrikes while civilians sought refuge in built bunkers. The entrance fee is 4 euros for adults and free for students. Visitors recommend bringing cash due to payment issues with cards. English-speaking guides offer informative tours, although some wish for more translated materials.
name: Flandernbunker

detail_description: Holstenstraße, one of the oldest streets in Kiel, connects the Karstadt department store in Vorstadt with the Nikolaikirche in Altstadt. After being heavily damaged during the war, it was reconstructed and became West Germany's first pedestrian street from 1953-1957. This traditional shopping mile is home to well-known international brands such as Foot Locker, TK Maxx, and Starbucks.
name: Holstenstraße

detail_description: Nestled in the heart of Kiel, TanTamar is a charming little restaurant that specializes in delightful Thai cuisine. With its cozy and family-friendly atmosphere, it's the perfect spot to escape the hustle and bustle of daily life for a relaxing evening. The menu boasts an impressive array of Asian dishes with a focus on authentic Thai flavors, including delicious vegetarian and vegan options. Guests can also enjoy a variety of refreshing cocktails alongside their meals.
name: TanTamar

excerpt:
Schilksee is a town on the Danish Wahld peninsula in the Kieler Förde. In 1959, the town was incorporated into the city of Kiel, therefore today sometimes named as Kiel-Schilksee.
The town is a popular vacation destination because of its beaches and houses several resorts. Wikipedia.
name: Schilksee

excerpt: Domed theatre with a program of 360° films on astronomical & scientific themes, plus kids’ shows.
detail_description: Nestled within the University of Applied Sciences in Kiel, Mediendom is a captivating 360-degree planetarium theater that promises an immersive experience for visitors of all ages. This unique dome theater not only aims to spark children's curiosity about astronomy and science through engaging interactive sessions but also serves as a cultural hub. With its comfortable seating arranged in three circles, guests can recline and enjoy stunning visual displays while listening to live performances, such as the enchanting 'Music of the Stars' concert.
name: Mediendom

detail_description: If you're looking for an exhilarating adventure, look no further than Final Escape - Live Escape Game Kiel. This captivating venue offers a unique experience where participants must solve intricate riddles to escape from locked rooms within a set time limit. Each room presents its own thrilling scenario, immersing you in a world of mystery and excitement. One standout option is the Magic School room, which has enchanted visitors with its clever puzzles and enchanting atmosphere reminiscent of beloved fantasy tales.
name: Final Escape - Live Escape Game Kiel

excerpt: Harborside cultural center on the site of old Kiel castle, with 3 multipurpose halls & a restaurant.
detail_description: Kieler Schloss is a harborside cultural center located on the historical site of the old Kiel castle. It features three multipurpose halls and a restaurant, making it a vibrant hub for various events and activities. The city of Kiel is renowned for hosting one of the world's biggest classical music festivals, with Kieler Schloss serving as an impressive venue alongside other notable locations such as the opera house, fjord-side stages, and the Howaldt shipyards.
name: Kieler Schloss (Kiel Castle)

excerpt: Unique museum in an industrial building featuring many historical engines, plus a lineup of events.
detail_description: The Machinery Museum Kiel Wik, located on Am Kiel-Kanal in Kiel, is a unique museum housed in an industrial building. It offers a fascinating insight into the history of machinery and features many historical engines. Visitors can explore the development of engines and mechanical history through its brilliant collection and displays. The museum also hosts events and provides special access to notable exhibits like the type23 submarine engine. Run by volunteers, it offers informative tours and is highly recommended for those interested in engineering marvels.
name: Machinery Museum Kiel Wik

detail_description: Anschar Park, located in the Wik district of Kiel, Schleswig-Holstein, is a green space that was once the site of Anschar Hospital. The hospital complex consisted of nearly 20 buildings including the main block, pavilions, chapel, and more. Today, only a few original structures remain amidst new apartments and offices. St. Peter's Church is nearby. The main hospital building now houses an art attic while another clinic building is being demolished.
name: Anschar Park

excerpt: Waterfront complex with club house & sports hall, hosting beach volleyball championships & regattas.
detail_description: The Olympic Center Schilksee Kiel Landeshauptadt is a stunning waterfront complex that includes a club house and sports hall, making it the perfect venue for beach volleyball championships and regattas. This sailing harbor served as a yacht harbor during the 1972 Olympics and offers facilities, restaurants, viewpoints, and even a bit of beach. Visitors can enjoy the gorgeous landscape while exploring adjacent attractions such as restaurants, cafes, and a promenade.
name: Olympic Center Schilksee Kiel Landeshauptadt

detail_description: Kieler Sprotte is a beloved dish in Kiel, a historic seaport. It features fresh Sprat, a fish similar to herring, caught during the fishing season and smoked by market vendors before being served as a snack. Additionally, it's mentioned that Sprotte is part of the Sprenger family's establishments and highly recommended. The dish holds cultural significance in Kiel and is enjoyed by locals and visitors alike.
name: Kieler Sprotte

excerpt: Historic botanical garden with a fountain, lawns, seating areas & an adjacent restaurant.
detail_description: The Old Botanical Garden in Kiel, opened in 1884, covers nearly 2.5 hectares of hilly terrain and features a charming mix of exotic plants including the Coast redwood, Dawn redwoods, Amur cork tree, and ginkgo tree. The garden offers a serene escape from city life with its lawns, seating areas, and a central fountain.
name: Old Botanical Garden, Kiel

excerpt: Museum for European art from the Renaissance to the present day, with painting, sculpture & video.
detail_description: The Art Gallery in Kiel is a must-visit for art enthusiasts, showcasing European art from the Renaissance to the present day. The museum boasts an extensive collection of paintings, sculptures, and videos. Additionally, Kiel's vibrant art scene includes modern galleries like the Kiel Municipal Gallery and Art Forum, featuring works by both local and international artists.
name: Art Gallery in Kiel

detail_description: Wunderino Arena, originally an aircraft hangar converted into a multipurpose hall in 1951, has become a North German success story. With a total area of 5000 square meters, it hosts a wide variety of events attracting around 1.5 million visitors annually. The arena is known for hosting diverse events such as handball matches, concerts, and shows like 'Holiday On Ice.'
name: Wunderino Arena

detail_description: Stadtmuseum Warleberger Hof is a historical gem located in the heart of Kiel. Housed in the oldest surviving building from the city's past, this museum offers a glimpse into Kiel's history during World War II and beyond. The noble residence, built in 1616, boasts exquisite features such as a sandstone portal, painted stucco ceilings, silk wallpaper, and 18th-century murals.
name: Stadtmuseum Warleberger Hof

excerpt: University computer history museum, including a giant 1958 Zuse Z11 machine, in a former war bunker.
detail_description: The Computermuseum der Fachhochschule Kiel is a unique museum located in a former war bunker, showcasing the history of computers. Visitors can explore the extensive collection that takes them on a journey from the roots of information technology in the 1960s to modern times. The museum features guided tours on Saturdays and offers an opportunity for self-guided exploration. The collection is carefully curated and includes unconventional attractions for all ages, such as a giant 1958 Zuse Z11 machine.
name: Computermuseum der Fachhochschule Kiel

detail_description: Schloßgarten is the starting point of the Kiellinie in its northeastern region. Visitors can indulge in delightful dining experiences at charming cafes and restaurants while admiring a small aquarium and observing the activities of sailing clubs.
name: Schloßgarten

excerpt: Wildlife park with forest & grassland areas, plus animal enclosures housing deer, wild boar & bison.
detail_description: Tiergehege Tannenberg is the largest wildlife park in Kiel, covering a vast 40-hectare area. Visitors can enjoy spending time in nature and observing animals such as deer, wild boar, bison, and other European wildlife species up close. While the park does not offer facilities and prohibits animal feeding, it provides a beautiful natural environment for leisurely walks and picturesque experiences.
name: Tiergehege Tannenberg

detail_description: Schleusen Kiel-Holtenau, located just a few kilometers north of the center of Kiel, is the starting point of the Kiel Canal, which is busier than both the Suez and Panama Canals. This man-made waterway has been in operation for over 120 years and serves as a crucial route for ships and recreational boats, saving them 460 kilometers on their journey around the Jutland Peninsula.
name: Schleusen Kiel-Holtenau

excerpt: Horse carriages & antique farm tools in a replica village with a windmill & craft workshops.
name: Open Air Museum Molfsee - State Museum of Ethnology

excerpt: Laboe is a municipality in the district of Plön, in Schleswig-Holstein, Germany. It is situated on the Baltic Sea coast, approximately 10 km northeast of Kiel. The Laboe Naval Memorial is located within the municipality, as is the U-boat U-995. Wikipedia.
name: Laboe

excerpt: Heikendorf is a municipality in the district of Plön, in Schleswig-Holstein, Germany. It is a seaside resort off the Baltic Sea, located approximately 10 km from Kiel. The oldest part of the town is the Old Viking settlement in Möltenort. Wikipedia.
detail_description: Heikendorf, a charming municipality in the district of Plön, Schleswig-Holstein, Germany, is a delightful seaside resort nestled along the Baltic Sea just 10 km from Kiel. The town boasts the historic Old Viking settlement in Möltenort as its oldest part.
name: Heikendorf

detail_description: Falckenstein Beach is located on the western shore of the Kiel Fjord, just north of the Kiel Canal. This natural beach boasts fine sand and fields of marram grass, offering a wonderful view of passing cruise ships and ferries. Accessible by ferry or bus, it provides spacious and clean surroundings for visitors to enjoy. With nearby parking, facilities, and cafes available, it's a suitable spot for families and those looking to relax by the water.
name: Falckenstein Beach

detail_description: I have been there many times, but only for the sailing boat parade.
name: Kieler Woche

excerpt: Striking 24-meter structure constructed in the 1890s from reclaimed bricks, with a lawn & benches.
name: Leuchtturm Kiel-Holtenau

detail_description: Schilksee Strandbad is a beautiful beach located along the estuary from Kiel. The white sands and clear waters make it an ideal spot for families and children to enjoy the sunshine. In addition to swimming, visitors can rent paddleboats in the summer. The beach area has a flowery promenade and park, providing a picturesque backdrop for leisurely strolls. While it can get crowded on hot days, there is ample free parking nearby.
name: Schilksee Strandbad

detail_description: Nestled at the northern edge of Kiel's historic old town, the Ratsdienergarten is the city's largest park, offering a delightful escape for both leisurely strolls and moments of relaxation. Bordered by Lorentzendamm and Jensendamm, this green oasis is flanked by Hiroshimapark to the west and Prinzengarten to the east. Visitors can admire statues commemorating Nobel Prize winners, highlighting the remarkable individuals connected to Kiel.
name: Ratsdienergarten

detail_description: The Bismarck Memorial Park, located at the Gettorf Oak, is a significant commemorative site. This park pays tribute to Bismarck and serves as a reminder of his historical influence. The memorial is situated amidst lush green surroundings and features various structures that honor his legacy. It stands as a symbol of admiration for his achievements and contributions to society. Visitors can explore this remarkable park, which offers an opportunity for reflection on the life and accomplishments of this influential figure in history.
name: Bismarck Denkmal an der Gettorfer Eiche

detail_description: The Holstein-Stadion, home to a successful team in the bundasliga 2 during the 2017/2018 season, offers ample parking and easy access. However, roadworks on the route from Hamburg to Kiel can hinder travel. Inside the stadium, fans can enjoy beer and food while browsing through a great and helpful fanshop.
name: Holstein-Stadion
